                            <comment id="78454" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 4 May 2012 07:09:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed from bug to improvement since the exception wasn&apos;t designed with that in mind. Would you be able to share which reporting framework has this requirement?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="78499" author="psfung" created="Sun, 6 May 2012 18:48:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;Changed from bug to improvement since the exception wasn&apos;t designed with that in mind.&lt;br/&gt;
I disagree. Java Throwable implements Serializable, the design of all exceptions should consider serializablity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;Would you be able to share which reporting framework has this requirement?&lt;br/&gt;
It is self developed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
